    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Learning to Live With Background Radiation</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peter G Puttre letter holds Miriam Goodman's June 25 letter missed significnce of concept of 'natural background radiation' (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Miriam Goodman seems to have missed the significance of the concept of ''natural background radiation.'' This radiation is present in nature without any contribution by man and we can do nothing about it. Any contamination that does not increase levels above ''natural background radiation'' is therefore not worthy of any further consideration.</p>
        <p>PETER G. PUTTRE  Manhasset</p>
      </block>
